This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10, Android enforces **edge-to-edge** display by default (following Android 15 requirements), and `AdjustResize` is fully deprecated at the platform level.

Here's what to do instead:

## 1. Use MAUI's built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll`

It's **on by default** in .NET 10. Make sure you haven't disabled it. If you have, re-enable it in `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
// Don't do this (disables auto-scroll):
// KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();
```

## 2. Structure your layout for it

`KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` works best when the focused input is inside a scrollable ancestor. For a chat screen, use a `Grid` layout:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <!-- Chat messages -->
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <!-- Input bar — this is what needs to move up -->
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..."
               HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" Command="{Binding SendCommand}" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

## 3. If auto-scroll alone isn't enough, handle insets manually

In `MainActivity.cs`, use the new `WindowInsets` API:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new InsetsListener());
}

private class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Bottom padding = keyboard height (if open) or nav bar height
        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

This listens for IME (keyboard) inset changes and adjusts the root view padding so your input bar is always visible above the keyboard.

**TL;DR:** Remove any `AdjustResize` calls, keep `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` enabled, and if that's not sufficient for your chat layout, add the `WindowInsets` listener above for precise control.
